---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import InteractiveCounter from '../components/islands/InteractiveCounter.astro';

const pageTitle = 'Astro Concepts Playground';
---

<BaseLayout pageTitle={pageTitle}>
  <h2>Astro in practice</h2>
  <p>
    This page is mostly static HTML (fast by default). The counter below is an isolated interactive section,
    demonstrating Astro's island mindset: add JavaScript only where needed.
  </p>

  <InteractiveCounter />

  <h3>Client directives (concept preview)</h3>
  <p>
    In production apps, directives like <code>client:load</code>, <code>client:idle</code>, and
    <code>client:visible</code> are used with framework components (React/Vue/Svelte) to control hydration timing.
  </p>

  <pre>{`<!-- Example usage with a framework component -->
<MyReactWidget client:visible />`}</pre>

  <p>
    Explore the <a href="/blog">Content Collections demo</a> and the <a href="/api/time.json">API endpoint</a>.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
